There was a link sent with reminder text re. 'manage my appointment on line' (which I went into) but no Video link was obvious there or in the text itself so I had to look at my history to access as I had used the video consultation before with the same clinic. Could have been problematic.   Video sometimes better than face to face especially for review given current safety issues and time saved by all and much better than just a phone call. Today I had met the clinician before which helps and I feel comfortable with her. That said, my previous consultation was with a young ST3 who I had not met before but he was relaxed and socially skilled and used the video facility well which is important in a first time consultation/meeting.  Some experiences of video consultations have been better than others. Quality of equipment varies? Some clinicians better than others at using the technology? (Advice & practice with feedback?) On a previous call with a different clinic, the consultant had his speaker volume on too high and I was getting feedback of my voice which was very off-putting to the detriment of the consultation I think.    I have been lucky in that the clinicians I have had video consultations with have been socially skilled and good listeners but I can think of some clinicians I have seen over recent years who have not had these attributes and fear that a video consultation would exaggerate these problems. Just a phone call would be much worse still in these cases.  I fear that a move to technology and away from face to face consultations could be to the detriment of marginalised, poorer and older people and should be done with care with this in mind (better still, we as a society should do something about marginalization and poverty of course!)

I think I would have been more embarrassed to talk through the issues in person and would have withheld concerns and questions which I would have taken away with me. I have been most thoroughly reassured in my approach to my medical condition.  Please maintain the option of video consultation for outpatient appointments for the longterm.  For me as a patient, where there us no examination necessary, they are far more efficient, and with the added bonus of saving travelling time to hospital clinic as well!
